      • runProcess

        public java.util.List<FinalBucketEntry> runProcess(int firstBucketNumber,
                                                   java.util.List<VaultEntry> entryList,
                                                   int wantedBucketSize)
                                            throws java.text.ParseException
        This method receives a list of VaultEntrys and a wanted step size (in minutes) for the resulting list of FinalBucketEntrys. In this method the given list of VaultEntrys will be transformed into a list of BucketEntrys through the createListOfBuckets method which will then be stripped-down to the necessary BucketEntrys via the removeUnneededBucketEntries method. The list of BucketEntrys will then run through the calculateAverageForSmallestBucketSize method to set all of the needed average calculations. The last step is to transform the list of BucketEntrys into a list of FinalBucketEntrys. If the wanted bucket size is 1 the list will just be transformed. If the wanted bucket size is greater than 1 the list will be sent through the !!!average to the wanted bucket size!!! method and reduced to the needed FinalBucketEntrys. If the given list of VaultEntrys results in a list of BucketEntrys that does not fulfill the given size % wanted size == 0 scheme the needed BucketEntrys will be added as empty BucketEntrys at the end of the list of BucketEntrys.
        Parameters:
        firstBucketNumber - starting index.
        entryList - The list of VaultEntrys that will be transformed into a list of FinalBucketEntrys.
        wantedBucketSize - This is the wanted bucket size (in minutes).
        Returns:
        This method returns a list of FinalBucketEntrys in the desired bucket size (time step size).
        Throws:
        java.text.ParseException

      • removeUnneededBucketEntries

        protected java.util.List<BucketEntry> removeUnneededBucketEntries(int firstBucketEntryNumber,
                                                                  java.util.List<BucketEntry> bucketList)
        This method iterates through all BucketEntrys of the given list of BucketEntrys and creates a new list of BucketEntrys that only contains the last found BucketEntry of each timestamp found in the given list of BucketEntrys. All the BucketEntrys in the new created list of BucketEntrys will have the correct numeration set to thier new position in the list. NEW: This method will now also update the listOfValuesForTheInterpolator list by setting the bucketNumbers inside this list to the new bucketNumber. This method might still create a return list with incorrect values for the interpolation. to be sure that the list is correct use the removeUnneededBucketEntries_old method.
        Parameters:
        firstBucketEntryNumber - This is the first BucketEntry number in the returned list.
        bucketList - This is the list of BucketEntrys that will be used to create the new normalized (minimal) list of BucketEntrys.
        Returns:
        This method returns a list of BucketEntrys with only one BucketEntry per timestamp.
